OL,6,FOfficial statistics released earlier
OL,7,Fthis year showed the estimated total
OL,8,Fnumber of people in relative low
OL,9,Fincome was at 14.35 million in the
OL,10,Fyear to March 2023, with some 4.33
OL,11,Fmillion of those being children.
OL,13,FThe latest figure for children was the
OL,14,Fhighest since comparable records for
OL,15,Fthe UK began, and prompted campaigners
OL,16,Fat the time to say young people are
OL,17,Fbeing failed and forgotten.
OL,19,FA household is considered to be in
OL,20,Frelative poverty if it is below 60% of
OL,21,Fthe median income after housing costs.
